==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Isohyetose
<hw>I`so*hy"e*tose`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Iso-</ets> + Gr. <grk>"yeto`s</grk> rain.]</ety> <fld>(Phys.
Geog.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to lines connecting places on the
earth's surface which have the same mean annual rainfall.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>An isohyetose line; called also
<altname>isohyet</altname>.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isolable</ent>⟦br⟧
